The key idea behind solving this problem with bit manipulation is as follows. A number N is a power of three, only when its binary representation has either one bit set to '1' at an odd position (1x) or all bits are set to '1'. In other words, a power of three will have a single bit set and be equal to the base of 3 raised to some exponent. This property makes it easier for us to check whether the input number is a power of three or not.

Here is a possible implementation of the solution in Java:

