        return (n & (n - 1)) == 0;
    } else {
        return false;
    }
}
```

In the above code, `isPowerOfThree()` checks two conditions to determine if the given input number is a power of three. Firstly, the method throws an exception for incorrect inputs like negative numbers, zero, or integers greater than MAX_VALUE divided by 3. Then, the method calculates the logarithm of the input number with respect to 3 using right shift operator, which keeps track of the highest significant bit value in the given number. Finally, the method verifies the bit pattern of the given number based on the properties mentioned earlier to decide whether the input number is a power of three or not.

